This paper discusses index coding problems with a specific structure on the side-information graphs, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also analyzes the structural properties of these graphs and provides an algorithm, which could fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of index codes, which could be related to network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to distributed computing and communication (cs.CC) due to the nature of the index coding problem.
